OL,6,FDuring the trial, a woman who
OL,7,Fwitnessed the incident described the
OL,8,Fdefendant as looking "possessed".JMiss
OL,9,FArthurs continued: "I felt like
OL,10,Fsomeone was trying to kill me. There
OL,11,Fwas such a sense of rage and anger in
OL,12,Fthe person who did this."
OL,14,FMiss Arthurs' friend who had also been
OL,15,Fin the toilets with her was able to
OL,16,Fget help and venue bouncers took
OL,17,FWilliams away.
OL,19,FMiss Arthurs' parents drove her to
OL,20,FMorriston Hospital where she was to
OL,21,Fspend the next three days.
