OL,6,FShe will serve two-thirds of the
OL,7,Fsentence in custody before being
OL,8,Freleased on licence to serve the
OL,9,Fremainder in the community.
OL,11,FShe was also made the subject of a
OL,12,Frestraining order banning her from
OL,13,Fcontacting her victim or posting
OL,14,Fanything about her on social media for
OL,15,Fthe next 10 years.
